    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/3815#discussion_r2071592471\n\nWith `workspace_required=true`, users can reasonably guess that it should do what it says: it should skip if there's no workspace. But some configs accidentally call `on_dir(nil)` in their `root_dir()` handler.\n\nRequiring a nil check in `root_dir()`, even when `workspace_required=true`, feels clumsy, and reduces the value of `workspace_required`.\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIf `workspace_required=true`, skip activation when `on_dir(nil)` is called, same as if `on_dir()` were *not* called.",
